<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><Section Number="0046.021" xmlns="http://StatRev.xsd"><Catchline xml:space="preserve">Actions; surviving death of party.</Catchline><SectionBody><Text xml:space="preserve" Style="Intro">No cause of action dies with the person. All causes of action survive and may be commenced, prosecuted, and defended in the name of the person prescribed by law.</Text></SectionBody><History xml:space="preserve">s. 30, Nov. 23, 1828; RS 989; GS 1375; RGS 2571; CGL 4211; s. 1, ch. 26541, 1951; s. 2, ch. 67-254.</History><Note><Text xml:space="preserve" Style="Intro">Former s. 45.11.</Text></Note></Section>